  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/5706",
  "title": "Add 'between' operator to the addNumericRefinement method",
  "body": "When using the API clients it's possible to pass a range of numeric filters.\r\nFor instance if I want to retrieve records with a price within 10 and 100, I just need to do.\r\n```\r\nindex.search('', {\r\n  filters: 'price:10 TO 100'\r\n}\r\n```\r\nIt would be nice to be able to do the same using the helpers' `addNumericRefinement` method.\r\nI was thinking that maybe it could be used that way\r\n\r\n## Basic example\r\n```\r\nhelper.addNumericRefinement('price', 'to', '10-100')\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Advanced example\r\n```\r\nhelper.addNumericRefinement('code', '=', '1');\r\nhelper.addNumericRefinement('price', 'to', ['1000-3000', '10-100']);\r\nhelper.setQuery('los');\r\nhelper.search();\r\n```\r\nwhich would be the same thing as doing \r\n```\r\nindex.search('los', {\r\n  filters: 'code=1 AND (price:1000 TO 3000 OR price:10 TO 100)'\r\n}\r\n```\r\nwhen using the JS API client",
